    <string name="market_garden">Market Garden</string>
    <string name="market_garden_intro_1">Operation Market-Garden
        \nAfter the successes encountered in the Normandy Breakout from July through August 1944, it was believed that the German Army was a beaten foe and in retreat.
        \nAs such, British General Montgomery lay forth a brazen plan to capture key bridges that would be required conquests for the final push into Germany, perhaps ending the war in Europe by Christmas of 1944.
        \nMontgomery relayed his plan and, following acceptance by Supreme Allied Commander in Europe - US General Dwight Eisenhower - put the plan into action.
        \nOn September 17th - just seven days after the official approval, Operation Market Garden was set in motion&#8230;</string>

